<HEAD>Police Officer Charged With Rape</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   WILKES-BARRE, Pa. (AP) _ A decorated veteran of the city police
force was charged Saturday with raping a woman who had called for
police help.
   Charles Warwick, 29, was arraigned before a district justice in
nearby Hanover Township on charges of rape, indecent assault and
official oppression. He was released after posting $25,000 bail.
   Warwick, who was decorated in 1987 and was one of two officers
attached to the city's K-9 dog unit, was indefinitely suspended
from his duties Friday, said police Chief Joseph Coyne.
   In an affidavit filed with the district justice, a 36-year-old
woman said she called for police Wednesday night because her drunk
boyfriend was threatening her and a friend.
   Another officer took the boyfriend into custody, while Warwick
stayed behind saying he would comfort the woman, according to the
affidavit. The woman claimed that Warwick, who lives down the
street from her, raped her later that night.
