<HEAD>Police Arrest 40 Skinheads in West German Brawl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOFHEIM, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fifty skinheads smashed a street
vendor's booth and attacked riot police with debris and bottles at
a festival near Frankfurt, authorities said Sunday.
   Police said 40 of the youths were arrested and that one
policeman and two rowdies were injured.
   Authorities said the violence began after the youths were
refused entry into a festival tent in Hofheim late Saturday. The
small town is 12 miles west of Frankfurt.
   The youths responded by storming and destroying a Turkish street
vendor's stand and blocking an intersection, police said.
   ``The youths could only be arrested after the repeated use of
police truncheons,'' a Frankfurt police official said.
   The official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said officers
were attacked with bottles and other debris before they arrested
the youths.
   He said the youths were charged with assault, resisting arrest
and destruction of property.
